# README

## Overview
This system detects suspicious activity using camera feeds and AI-based image analysis.  
It can identify masked individuals, compare detections with recent alerts/news, and send WhatsApp notifications using Twilio.

---

# Running the System

To start the system:

1. Double-click the batch file:
start_entry.bat

2. The script will automatically:
- Start the server
- Launch Ollama
- Open the website interface

---

# Demo / Testing

You can test the system using the preloaded example recordings and detections included in the project.

---

# AI Model Configuration

The system currently uses the MoonDream model through Ollama because it requires relatively low memory.

You may switch to a more powerful model if your machine has enough resources.

To change the model:
- Update the Batch file configuration
- Update the Ollama configuration file accordingly

---

# WhatsApp Notifications (Twilio)

To receive WhatsApp alerts, you must create a Twilio account.

After creating the account:

1. Open the .env file
2. Insert your Twilio credentials

Example:
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=your_twilio_number
TARGET_PHONE_NUMBER=your_phone_number

⚠️ Important:
- Do NOT share your .env file
- Do NOT upload credentials to GitHub
- The current file may still contain development credentials and should be replaced immediately

---

# Alert Types

## Regular Alert

When a masked person is detected:
Masked Person Detected on ${camTitle}!

---

## Serious Threat Alert

A serious threat alert is triggered when:
- A masked person is detected
AND
- There is related intelligence from:
  - Recent news reports
  - WhatsApp reports
  - Events reported within the last 24 hours

OR

- The detection occurs in an area with a recently reported incident

Message example:
Warning - serious threat!!!

---

# Security Notes

- Never expose:
  - .env
  - .git
  - API tokens
  - Twilio credentials

- Make sure sensitive files are included in .gitignore

Recommended additions:
.env
.git
node_modules

---

# Requirements

- Ollama installed and running
- Twilio account (optional for WhatsApp alerts)
- Internet connection for news/WhatsApp integrations
- Supported AI model installed locally

---

# Recommended Models

Lightweight:
- MoonDream

More powerful alternatives:
- LLaVA
- Qwen-VL
- Other Ollama vision-compatible models